{"id": "EUVD-2022-54579", "enisaUuid": "e3853303-6e0b-3492-aed8-a3dd97bfc2db", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ni2c: piix4: Fix a memory leak in the EFCH MMIO support\n\nThe recently added support for EFCH MMIO regions introduced a memory\nleak in that code path. The leak is caused by the fact that\nrelease_resource() merely removes the resource from the tree but does\nnot free its memory. We need to call release_mem_region() instead,\nwhich does free the memory. As a nice side effect, this brings back\nsome symmetry between the legacy and MMIO paths.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T02:23:54", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:36:48", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d2bf1a6480e8d44658a8ac3bdcec081238873212", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a3263e4cf8265f0c9eb0ed8a9b50f132c7a42e19", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8ad59b397f86a4d8014966fdc0552095a0c4fb2b"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49653"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "02f4f0e8-ab33-34f6-bd73-8f138454d1e6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7c148722d074c29fb998578eea5de3c14b9608c9 <a3263e4cf8265f0c9eb0ed8a9b50f132c7a42e19"}, {"id": "0cf84e83-bf5e-3301-b813-4366dc742bd2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.11"}, {"id": "6da2783a-e55d-3279-a15c-a3f9457d8880", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "840b108f-adf0-32bc-b090-3b8ed6921f11", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.54"}, {"id": "d6be683b-ec1f-31b0-af87-3fcf1d8f2c24", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.18"}, {"id": "e1065444-53a7-3dc8-9a76-1ac1dbcff135", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f48190bca4b1a397f2e050efea2c8e8e72049ec8"}, {"id": "e8053fd3-0259-304c-83e3-3bfd827ffd98", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "pa